text.paragraph:
Pediatric patients may be more susceptible to systemic toxicity from equivalent doses due to their larger skin surface to body mass ratios (see 
                              PRECAUTIONS – Pediatric Use
                           ).

list.item:
 Parents of pediatric patients should be advised not to use Mometasone Furoate Cream 0.1% in the treatment of diaper dermatitis. Mometasone Furoate Cream 0.1% should not be applied in the diaper area as diapers or plastic pants may constitute occlusive dressing (see 
   DOSAGE & ADMINISTRATION
).
